# Cursor Rules — Life Command Center

> **CRITICAL: Read .github/AI_INSTRUCTIONS.md before modifying any files in /api/.**

## Vercel Hobby Plan Constraint

This project has a HARD LIMIT of 12 serverless functions (12 .js files in /api/).
We are currently AT the limit with exactly 12 files. Creating a 13th file will break
the deployment and cause a production 404 error.

## Rules

1. NEVER create new .js files directly in /api/
2. Add new endpoints as sub-routes to existing functions (use ?action= or ?_route= patterns)
3. Put new helper code in /api/_shared/ or /api/_handlers/ (not counted as functions)
4. After ANY change to /api/, verify: `ls api/*.js | wc -l` outputs 12 or less
5. Update vercel.json rewrites when adding new sub-routes
6. Use descriptive commit messages — never "GPT changes" or similar generic messages
7. See .github/AI_INSTRUCTIONS.md for full architecture, routing, and design principles
8. NEVER set LCC_API_KEY in Vercel env vars — no frontend auth flow exists yet; setting it breaks all data endpoints with 401s
